{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01B8MyQNihuebqfSqqGGYM6J","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is in order. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Findings:**\n- The RS had been externally expanded from 3 to 5 members (StatefulSet scaled to 5 replicas, pods 3 and 4 added to the RS)\n- The ConfigMap existed with baseline settings (verbosity=1, slowms=200) but was **not mounted** — pods were using raw CLI flags with no config file\n\n**Changes applied:**\n\n| Setting | Before | After |\n|---|---|---|\n| `systemLog.verbosity` | 1 | **2** (+1 level) |\n| `operationProfiling.slowOpThresholdMs` | 200 ms | **400 ms** (2×) |\n| `wiredTiger.engineConfig.journalCompressor` | snappy (default, no config) | **zlib** |\n| RS member count | 5 | **3** (target restored) |\n\n**Steps taken:**\n1. Updated the `mongod-config` ConfigMap with verbosity=2, slowms=400, journalCompressor=zlib\n2. Removed RS members 3 and 4 one-at-a-time via `rs.reconfig()` (MongoDB only allows removing 1 voting member per reconfig)\n3. Patched the StatefulSet to scale to 3 replicas, mount the ConfigMap at `/etc/mongod`, and start mongod with `--config /etc/mongod/mongod.conf`\n4. Waited for the rolling restart to complete — all 3 pods now run with the config file\n5. Verified: verbosity=2, slowms=400, journalCompressor=zlib on all 3 members; RS healthy with 1 PRIMARY + 2 SECONDARY"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":322,"cache_read_input_tokens":57352,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":322},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ce865e51-870f-4936-9278-33d18db022f7","uuid":"8a88b308-237b-411a-8b21-17ef919aadbf","request_id":"req_011CccM7Lmj9a5KfH7TY6BFV"}
